  "finger_focus": "Engineering prose tempo",
  "guided": true,
  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "No new keys today. Technical prose lives or dies on a steady tempo - the unfamiliar term gets the same even beat as the plain word around it. Three words, each repeated at one level pace."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Hands on the home row, thumbs over the space bar, eyes off the keys. Repeat each word without hurrying. When a long term tempts you to slow, count it through: one, two, three, four."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "metronome",
      "title": "Even hands",
      "text": "A clear technical passage never lurches; it holds its pace so the reader keeps up. Same gap between every keystroke, term or no term. The even hand is the one that does not lose the thread."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "latency latency latency latency latency",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Rhythm: latency",
      "hint": "Repeat at one tempo: latency - latency - latency. Hold the gaps equal."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "baseline baseline baseline baseline",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: baseline",
      "hint": "Repeat steadily, no jerks: baseline - baseline - baseline."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "restoring restoring restoring",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: restoring",
      "hint": "Repeat evenly: restoring - restoring - restoring. Do not speed up at the end."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Let the hand take even the technical word in one motion, the way you read a term you have typed all week. Even repetition turns motion into habit - and the habit holds when the sentence runs long and dense."
    },
    {
      "type": "pullquote",
      "text": "Loosen your shoulders and wrists, picture the metronome, and let rhythm set the pace. Don't look down - you lose the thought.",
      "by": "Eleanor Hayes, editor"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "All three done? Open the trainer below and take one clean run at the full lesson text. That run saves your progress and unlocks the next lesson."
    }
  ],
